<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id46c6af3b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s6313"><num value="6313">§ 6313.</num><heading> Fractional parts of a cent</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In the payment of any tax imposed by this title, a fractional part of a cent shall be disregarded unless it amounts to one-half cent or more, in which case it shall be increased to 1 cent.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id46c6af3c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/778">68A Stat. 778</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/94/455/tXIX/s1906/a/19">Pub. L. 94–455, title XIX, § 1906(a)(19)</ref>, <date date="1976-10-04">Oct. 4, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/1825">90 Stat. 1825</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
